articles.text:
A video of a teacher scolding her pupil in a classroom, which is going viral on Twitter has left users of the platform divided.

The teacher could be seen trying to make the child write a sum on the board. Her effort also included smacking the child who apparently didn’t understand what she was being told to do.

The teacher’s method was frowned at by many after the video was shared on Twitter with the aim of reporting her to the Domestic and Sexual Violence Response Team.

However, some didn’t find anything wrong with her method as they revealed that they passed through the same to get to where they are today.

One Twitter user, @AkanPatrick1, said, “The fact that it happened to us doesn’t make it right. The world has changed. There are better ways to teach and not behave like cavemen.”

@perrzy1 said, “She is frustrated clearly, she couldn’t control her emotions but she doesn’t hate that child. She simply needs more training. You simply don’t understand the enormous pressure on private school teachers. Regardless of the situation, children shouldn’t be treated that way.”

The sharing of the video as done by @Gidi_Traffic was found to be mischievous by @Anthonykenechi1 who tweeted, “You may not be happy with the approach of the teaching. But she is doing it for the girl favour. But, the teacher should also know that we have slow learners.”

@GbolahanOsoneye replied, “No child can learn under pressure and fear…there are better ways of teaching without being wicked,”

@Oluwatosindebo3 said, “Teaching is not easy ooo, especially when the student isn’t getting it right, she can choose to ignore but she just wants to try all her possible best to ensure the child gets it right at all cost.”

According to @metrumery, “Some people who have never taught before are here talking nonsense. They are different kinds of students and they all assimilate differently. What the teacher did isn’t that bad. It’s a class of about 40 students, and I bet they will be more than one with such dull nature.”

@drangie_bae said, “She may just have a learning disability. All the pinching/beating in the world would not solve it. Quite sad. She needs extra lessons. I know of someone that had something similar. He just couldn’t understand maths. But with extra lessons and no beating, he became a math guru.”

@Teamjhybo said, “I cannot believe the people on this thread that think it’s ACCEPTABLE for a teacher to Continually pinch a smack a child. The child is terrified she won’t learn any faster, if anything she will be thinking of where the next pinch or slap is going to come from. What RUBBISH.”

@Babsfrey said, “Clearly, she’s frustrated. I don’t think she hates the child. I’ve seen parents do this to their kids too. She needs more training to deal with her emotions and change teaching styles to suit the child’s unique needs”
